parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A fuel tank leak or failure can cause a hazardous condition, potentially leading to fires, explosions, or accidents, which can result in serious injury or death.
symptoms: Gasoline smell inside or outside the vehicle
gasoline leaking from underneath the vehicle
fuel tank leak of unknown origin
fuel tank warped or damaged
flange seal failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Failure to Notify Owners of Fuel Tank Defect
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Jaguar's failure to notify owners of the fuel tank defect can lead to a delay in repairs, increasing the risk of accidents or fires.
symptoms: Owners not informed of fuel tank defect
no recall or technical service bulletin issued
dealerships aware of the problem but not notifying owners.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Inadequate Repair of Fuel Tank Leak
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Inadequate repair of the fuel tank leak can lead to recurring problems, increasing the risk of accidents or fires.
symptoms: Temporary repairs
such as replacing the flange seal
do not address the underlying issue
fuel tank leak persists after repair
dealerships unable to guarantee the repair.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unintended acceleration of the vehicle when braking can lead to accidents, injuries, and even fatalities, as the driver loses control of the vehicle.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates unexpectedly when the brake pedal is applied
the vehicle takes off suddenly
the vehicle fails to stop or slow down when braking
the engine revs at high speed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden and catastrophic failure of Continental tires can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Tire tread separation
sidewall bulging
cord separation
vibration
and sudden blowout failure
often at high speeds.
